1
00:00:06,065 --> 00:00:09,865
<i>You have two weeks</i>
<i>to make her fall for you.</i>

2
00:00:09,945 --> 00:00:13,025
<i>Like she's counting down</i>
<i>the time she has with Piang.</i>

3
00:00:13,105 --> 00:00:14,785
I love you.

4
00:00:15,425 --> 00:00:17,985
<i>I lost a family member.</i>

5
00:00:18,065 --> 00:00:20,705
She was my twin sister.

6
00:00:20,785 --> 00:00:23,305
<i>So I don't deserve to be happy either.</i>

7
00:00:23,385 --> 00:00:24,425
Let's break up.

8
00:00:24,505 --> 00:00:26,345
<i>So why, when it comes to us,</i>

9
00:00:26,425 --> 00:00:27,705
<i>are you the one letting go?</i>

10
00:00:27,785 --> 00:00:29,625
<i>Have you ever felt anything for me?</i>

11
00:00:29,705 --> 00:00:32,505
This is my answer.

12
00:01:29,385 --> 00:01:32,785
Song doesn't love me back, Grandma.

13
00:01:35,385 --> 00:01:36,785
I give up.

14
00:01:42,425 --> 00:01:45,145
I give up, Grandma.

15
00:01:49,025 --> 00:01:51,025
I give up.

16
00:03:05,185 --> 00:03:06,905
<i>Do you love me?</i>

17
00:03:09,185 --> 00:03:10,825
Please don't stay silent.

18
00:05:07,785 --> 00:05:11,465
Song, What's wrong, my dear?

19
00:05:12,225 --> 00:05:14,305
Have you been drinking?

20
00:05:48,225 --> 00:05:50,585
May I come in, my dear?

21
00:05:51,665 --> 00:05:53,465
Grandma, what's wrong?

22
00:05:54,345 --> 00:05:57,625
You don't seem like yourself,

23
00:05:57,705 --> 00:05:59,585
so I wanted to ask

24
00:05:59,665 --> 00:06:03,065
if there's anything you'd like
to tell me, my dear.

25
00:06:04,385 --> 00:06:05,585
No.

26
00:06:07,025 --> 00:06:08,785
I just need some time.

27
00:06:10,265 --> 00:06:12,145
Please give me some time, Grandma.

28
00:06:14,665 --> 00:06:18,425
Song, you know

29
00:06:18,505 --> 00:06:21,425
you can tell me anything.

30
00:06:25,625 --> 00:06:26,625
Okay.

31
00:06:26,705 --> 00:06:29,225
Then I won't push you.

32
00:06:29,745 --> 00:06:33,185
I'll give you all the time you need.

33
00:06:33,745 --> 00:06:37,865
But, I'd like to send someone

34
00:06:37,945 --> 00:06:41,025
to keep you company, my dear.

35
00:07:21,025 --> 00:07:22,345
Can I sleep with you?

36
00:07:38,305 --> 00:07:40,025
Get some sleep, Piang.

37
00:07:43,385 --> 00:07:45,545
It was just a bad dream.

38
00:08:53,505 --> 00:08:56,265
Could you check on your sister?

39
00:08:56,345 --> 00:08:59,065
She hasn't eaten since yesterday.

40
00:08:59,145 --> 00:09:01,425
I have a meeting this morning, Grandma.

41
00:09:03,705 --> 00:09:05,305
I'll get going.

42
00:09:05,385 --> 00:09:07,825
Is your work really
more important than your sister?

43
00:09:16,545 --> 00:09:19,185
Maybe you should
ask yourself that question.

44
00:09:21,465 --> 00:09:23,105
At this point,

45
00:09:24,185 --> 00:09:28,665
what you want or how Piang feels,

46
00:09:30,265 --> 00:09:31,785
which matters more.

47
00:09:35,945 --> 00:09:37,145
I'll get going.

48
00:10:03,985 --> 00:10:07,305
I'm going to the café, Grandma.

49
00:10:07,385 --> 00:10:09,505
I haven't been there since the accident.

50
00:10:09,585 --> 00:10:11,625
I wonder how it's doing.

51
00:10:12,425 --> 00:10:13,905
Are you sure you're okay?

52
00:10:15,825 --> 00:10:16,985
I am.

53
00:10:18,425 --> 00:10:21,625
I don't want my sadness
to ruin everything.

54
00:10:22,225 --> 00:10:25,785
Besides, working makes me feel worthy

55
00:10:26,545 --> 00:10:29,105
and love myself more.

56
00:10:31,385 --> 00:10:34,465
So I won't have to chase
anyone's love again.

57
00:10:36,865 --> 00:10:38,545
I'll get going.

58
00:10:57,625 --> 00:11:01,025
Here's our signature drink.

59
00:11:01,105 --> 00:11:02,505
Are you tired?

60
00:11:08,225 --> 00:11:10,345
Your matcha latte is ready.

61
00:11:11,425 --> 00:11:12,985
Please give it a try.

62
00:11:21,785 --> 00:11:25,025
Hey!
Didn't I tell you I'm allergic to dairy?

63
00:11:25,105 --> 00:11:26,585
Why did you put it in?

64
00:11:27,505 --> 00:11:28,825
If something happens to me,

65
00:11:28,905 --> 00:11:30,425
I'll sue the hell out of you.

66
00:11:32,145 --> 00:11:33,465
I'm so sorry.

67
00:11:33,545 --> 00:11:35,105
I'm the café manager.

68
00:11:35,185 --> 00:11:37,825
I sincerely apologize for this mistake.

69
00:11:37,905 --> 00:11:40,425
We'll take full responsibility
for the damages.

70
00:11:41,025 --> 00:11:42,545
With such an idiot working here,

71
00:11:42,625 --> 00:11:44,265
you're going to get someone killed!

72
00:11:44,345 --> 00:11:46,625
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

73
00:11:49,505 --> 00:11:51,745
Piang, are you okay?

74
00:11:51,825 --> 00:11:53,545
You're soaked. Go clean yourself up.

75
00:11:53,625 --> 00:11:54,865
Go on.

76
00:12:01,305 --> 00:12:02,585
Thanks.

77
00:12:02,665 --> 00:12:04,985
Piang's back. Don't worry.

78
00:12:05,065 --> 00:12:06,065
Mm.

79
00:12:14,785 --> 00:12:16,745
I thought you said you were okay.

80
00:12:18,505 --> 00:12:20,465
I really tried.

81
00:12:21,505 --> 00:12:23,465
But I can't do it.

82
00:12:25,465 --> 00:12:26,545
I know.

83
00:12:26,625 --> 00:12:28,065
Come on. Have a seat.

84
00:12:46,065 --> 00:12:47,185
Hey.

85
00:12:48,305 --> 00:12:50,945
It's okay if someone doesn't love you,

86
00:12:51,545 --> 00:12:53,785
because you still have Mudmee,

87
00:12:54,385 --> 00:12:56,185
and…

88
00:12:58,265 --> 00:12:59,265
you have me too.

89
00:13:01,945 --> 00:13:03,465
Grandma.

90
00:13:07,025 --> 00:13:10,185
I've played a part in
what happened to you.

91
00:13:11,545 --> 00:13:14,985
But you have to understand
everything I did

92
00:13:15,065 --> 00:13:17,505
was because I truly
wanted the best for you.

93
00:13:19,545 --> 00:13:21,265
I understand.

94
00:13:21,945 --> 00:13:25,185
But none of this is your fault, Grandma.

95
00:13:28,065 --> 00:13:30,065
It's because of Song.

96
00:13:36,865 --> 00:13:38,665
If she loved me

97
00:13:38,745 --> 00:13:40,865
and was willing to fight beside me,

98
00:13:41,465 --> 00:13:44,065
I would've never given up.

99
00:13:45,465 --> 00:13:47,385
I know.

100
00:13:47,465 --> 00:13:49,465
That's true.

101
00:13:52,545 --> 00:13:55,225
I should thank you

102
00:13:56,905 --> 00:13:59,465
for opening up to me so honestly.

103
00:14:00,545 --> 00:14:05,745
I never thought
I'd hear those words from you.

104
00:14:09,065 --> 00:14:10,225
Well,

105
00:14:12,505 --> 00:14:14,385
you should thank me,

106
00:14:14,465 --> 00:14:17,305
because it wasn't easy for me to say them.

107
00:14:25,465 --> 00:14:27,145
Grandma,

108
00:14:28,465 --> 00:14:30,825
I'll do as you said.

109
00:14:32,865 --> 00:14:35,465
I'll get over her

110
00:14:37,225 --> 00:14:41,225
and become the old Piangrawin
again as soon as I can.

111
00:14:45,305 --> 00:14:47,265
You don't have to rush.

112
00:14:49,025 --> 00:14:49,865
Just let it be.

113
00:14:50,785 --> 00:14:52,585
Give yourself time.

114
00:14:52,665 --> 00:14:54,945
It's okay if you fall apart
a little longer.

115
00:15:00,745 --> 00:15:02,385
Really?

116
00:15:06,065 --> 00:15:08,385
Seeing you hurt this much,

117
00:15:09,065 --> 00:15:11,945
I guess I have to stop forcing you,

118
00:15:12,025 --> 00:15:13,945
and your sister too.

119
00:15:18,745 --> 00:15:21,625
I guess it's time

120
00:15:21,705 --> 00:15:26,945
for me to let you both feel

121
00:15:27,785 --> 00:15:31,185
what you truly want to feel.

122
00:15:34,185 --> 00:15:37,265
Grandma, thank you.

123
00:16:19,545 --> 00:16:21,345
I'm hurting with you now, Neung.

124
00:16:21,985 --> 00:16:23,745
You don't have to hurt alone anymore.

125
00:17:37,425 --> 00:17:40,745
Is this really Song, my little sister?

126
00:17:44,385 --> 00:17:46,425
You love that woman, don't you?

127
00:18:03,385 --> 00:18:04,585
I'm sorry.

128
00:18:05,345 --> 00:18:07,825
I promised myself
I'd never love anyone again.

129
00:18:09,145 --> 00:18:10,945
I didn't want to be selfish,

130
00:18:11,585 --> 00:18:15,785
finding happiness after you were gone,
while you left with so much pain.

131
00:18:16,825 --> 00:18:19,145
Are you suffering like this

132
00:18:19,225 --> 00:18:20,585
because of me?

133
00:18:21,185 --> 00:18:22,385
No.

134
00:18:23,985 --> 00:18:26,145
It's because of me.

135
00:18:28,905 --> 00:18:31,225
I still can't let go.

136
00:18:32,585 --> 00:18:35,185
Then stop doing this to yourself.

137
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:38,145
Stop holding on,

138
00:18:40,265 --> 00:18:42,705
and stop running from your heart.

139
00:19:00,425 --> 00:19:04,345
In life, we don't get many chances, Song.

140
00:19:05,825 --> 00:19:09,825
When we find someone we love,
and they truly love us back,

141
00:19:11,865 --> 00:19:14,185
we should hold on to them tight.

142
00:19:17,825 --> 00:19:19,185
And…

143
00:19:35,505 --> 00:19:39,825
Please be happy for your big sister.

144
00:19:48,105 --> 00:19:49,385
Can you do that?

145
00:19:55,865 --> 00:19:59,505
You promised me. Don't let me down.

146
00:20:18,385 --> 00:20:19,385
Neung.

147
00:20:38,945 --> 00:20:42,785
<i>In life, we don't get many chances, Song.</i>

148
00:20:44,745 --> 00:20:46,185
Please be happy

149
00:20:47,225 --> 00:20:49,065
for your big sister.

150
00:21:39,745 --> 00:21:43,865
Well, that's a satisfying sound.

151
00:21:43,945 --> 00:21:45,625
Very refreshing.

152
00:21:46,225 --> 00:21:50,185
-Grandma.
-Song, come here, my dear.

153
00:21:50,265 --> 00:21:53,745
If you want a drink, I'll drink with you.

154
00:21:53,825 --> 00:21:57,025
I may not know

155
00:21:57,105 --> 00:22:00,265
what you're going through right now,

156
00:22:00,345 --> 00:22:02,185
but more importantly,

157
00:22:02,265 --> 00:22:04,105
the two of us, grandmother
and granddaughter,

158
00:22:04,185 --> 00:22:06,785
will get through this together.

159
00:22:06,865 --> 00:22:09,345
Come on, help yourself.

160
00:22:09,425 --> 00:22:12,265
Whichever bottle or flavor you like,

161
00:22:12,345 --> 00:22:14,905
feel free to pick one.

162
00:22:14,985 --> 00:22:15,985
Go ahead.

163
00:22:17,425 --> 00:22:18,905
I'm not drinking anymore, Grandma.

164
00:22:18,985 --> 00:22:19,865
Huh?

165
00:22:19,945 --> 00:22:21,505
Why not, my dear?

166
00:22:22,585 --> 00:22:24,025
I dreamed about Neung.

167
00:22:24,105 --> 00:22:26,065
She gave me a reality check

168
00:22:26,145 --> 00:22:29,825
and made me realize
how I should face what I'm going through.

169
00:22:29,905 --> 00:22:31,665
Poor you.

170
00:22:31,745 --> 00:22:33,585
See?

171
00:22:33,665 --> 00:22:36,065
Neung must be worried about you,

172
00:22:36,145 --> 00:22:41,385
just like your grandma is.

173
00:22:42,545 --> 00:22:44,185
Grandma.

174
00:22:47,145 --> 00:22:48,305
All right, enough.

175
00:22:48,385 --> 00:22:50,345
No more drama.

176
00:22:51,425 --> 00:22:54,705
Instead, help me out.

177
00:22:54,785 --> 00:22:58,225
I went through
all the trouble of lining these up.

178
00:22:58,305 --> 00:23:01,145
So let's have a drink-off.

179
00:23:01,225 --> 00:23:02,425
Let's finish them all.

180
00:23:02,505 --> 00:23:05,505
I can't be bothered
putting them back on the shelf.

181
00:23:05,585 --> 00:23:07,945
-Okay?
-Really?

182
00:23:08,025 --> 00:23:11,665
Since you asked so directly,
I'll be honest. The answer is no.

183
00:23:13,065 --> 00:23:14,625
The truth is,

184
00:23:14,705 --> 00:23:17,825
I've been craving a drink for days.

185
00:23:17,905 --> 00:23:22,425
Come on, let's finish these together.

186
00:23:22,505 --> 00:23:27,505
Pick any flavor
or any drink you like, be my guest.

187
00:23:27,585 --> 00:23:28,865
Come on.

188
00:23:29,905 --> 00:23:31,065
Okay.

189
00:23:32,505 --> 00:23:33,705
Go ahead.

190
00:23:33,785 --> 00:23:34,865
Okay.

191
00:23:43,025 --> 00:23:44,625
Another one.

192
00:23:45,225 --> 00:23:46,745
Coming right up, boss.

193
00:23:47,425 --> 00:23:48,385
You got it.

194
00:23:50,945 --> 00:23:54,505
Undefeated.

195
00:24:11,865 --> 00:24:13,465
<i>I need to talk to you.</i>

196
00:24:24,745 --> 00:24:25,665
<i>Are you asleep?</i>

197
00:24:41,705 --> 00:24:44,705
<i>I'm sorry for saying that.</i>

198
00:25:01,105 --> 00:25:04,585
So your grandma
has finally accepted you and Song.

199
00:25:05,665 --> 00:25:09,065
Yes, but what does it matter
if Song isn't interested?

200
00:25:09,145 --> 00:25:12,745
I'm not chasing her for love anymore.

201
00:25:12,825 --> 00:25:15,145
I love myself a lot more now.

202
00:25:15,225 --> 00:25:16,265
Really?

203
00:25:16,345 --> 00:25:19,265
Yeah. If we ever get back together,

204
00:25:21,145 --> 00:25:23,505
I'll make her chase me instead.

205
00:25:23,585 --> 00:25:25,185
I'll teach her a lesson.

206
00:25:30,465 --> 00:25:31,865
But then again,

207
00:25:33,105 --> 00:25:35,065
that'll probably never happen.

208
00:25:36,145 --> 00:25:37,625
You never know.

209
00:25:38,225 --> 00:25:41,425
When I came in,
I think I saw her watching you.

210
00:25:42,345 --> 00:25:43,265
Where?

211
00:25:47,865 --> 00:25:49,865
Where's Song? Song!

212
00:25:50,625 --> 00:25:52,465
Song, where are you?

213
00:26:01,545 --> 00:26:04,585
You said you'd make her chase you,

214
00:26:05,265 --> 00:26:08,345
but the second you heard her name,
you ran off instead.

215
00:26:09,025 --> 00:26:11,225
Don't joke like that. I'm already sad.

216
00:26:11,305 --> 00:26:12,585
I'm not joking.

217
00:26:12,665 --> 00:26:14,185
I really saw her.

218
00:26:14,865 --> 00:26:19,025
If Song comes to win you back,
make her work for it.

219
00:26:20,625 --> 00:26:22,585
I'm going to the restroom.

220
00:26:47,225 --> 00:26:49,625
I'M SORRY FOR WHAT I SAID.

221
00:26:56,225 --> 00:26:59,425
I'M SORRY FOR WHAT I SAID.
I REALLY LOVE YOU.

222
00:27:04,785 --> 00:27:06,465
Oh, Song.

223
00:27:11,505 --> 00:27:13,945
<i>I'm sorry for what I said.</i>

224
00:27:14,025 --> 00:27:16,185
<i>I really love you.</i>

225
00:27:16,265 --> 00:27:17,465
Hey!

226
00:27:18,745 --> 00:27:20,305
Why didn't you come in?

227
00:27:20,905 --> 00:27:23,265
I'M SORRY FOR WHAT I SAID.
I REALLY LOVE YOU.

228
00:27:23,345 --> 00:27:24,425
Damn.

229
00:27:25,105 --> 00:27:27,185
I'll be right in.

230
00:27:30,825 --> 00:27:31,905
Mon, get over here.

231
00:27:31,985 --> 00:27:33,225
-Sorry.
-Sorry.

232
00:27:33,305 --> 00:27:35,745
-What's going on?
-Look at this.

233
00:27:39,305 --> 00:27:41,625
Tell me your plan.

234
00:27:42,465 --> 00:27:43,665
Sure thing.

235
00:27:43,745 --> 00:27:46,905
I guarantee this is going to be fun.

236
00:27:47,665 --> 00:27:48,865
Let's do it.

237
00:27:56,945 --> 00:28:01,825
<i>Everyone, this is Piang. I need your help.</i>

238
00:28:05,585 --> 00:28:06,785
126 FOOD

239
00:28:42,945 --> 00:28:44,225
<i>Hello, Ple.</i>

240
00:28:45,585 --> 00:28:46,545
Mm.

241
00:28:48,305 --> 00:28:51,705
What are you doing? Am I bothering you?

242
00:28:53,745 --> 00:28:55,505
Not at all. What's up?

243
00:29:00,905 --> 00:29:03,225
What do you think of Piang's plan?

244
00:29:07,625 --> 00:29:09,625
I was going to help her. What about you?

245
00:29:10,345 --> 00:29:11,945
<i>I'm going to help her too.</i>

246
00:29:12,545 --> 00:29:16,425
But, are you okay with seeing me again?

247
00:29:19,145 --> 00:29:20,425
Of course.

248
00:29:21,025 --> 00:29:22,665
I can separate the two.

249
00:29:26,465 --> 00:29:27,425
Okay.

250
00:29:28,425 --> 00:29:32,025
But I think when we're around everyone,

251
00:29:32,625 --> 00:29:35,145
we should pretend we're still together.

252
00:29:35,825 --> 00:29:36,985
<i>Why?</i>

253
00:29:37,585 --> 00:29:39,905
If Piang and Song find out
we've broken up,

254
00:29:39,985 --> 00:29:42,505
they'll feel bad asking us for help.

255
00:29:42,585 --> 00:29:45,545
<i>I think</i>
<i>we should wait until their plan succeeds,</i>

256
00:29:45,625 --> 00:29:48,105
<i>then tell them when the time is right.</i>

257
00:29:49,545 --> 00:29:50,545
Mm.

258
00:29:51,105 --> 00:29:52,345
Then it's settled.

259
00:29:53,985 --> 00:29:55,545
Is that all? I'm hanging up.

260
00:29:55,625 --> 00:29:56,945
But, Ple…

261
00:30:00,185 --> 00:30:02,625
Is your dad still harassing you?

262
00:30:03,225 --> 00:30:04,105
Not anymore.

263
00:30:06,145 --> 00:30:07,065
<i>Okay.</i>

264
00:30:07,585 --> 00:30:09,185
I'll hang up then.

265
00:31:17,585 --> 00:31:20,065
I'M SORRY FOR WHAT I SAID.
I REALLY LOVE YOU.

266
00:31:20,145 --> 00:31:21,505
Shit.

267
00:31:46,425 --> 00:31:48,025
-Yes, Boss.
<i>-Song.</i>

268
00:31:48,105 --> 00:31:49,785
<i>Piang's been in another accident.</i>

269
00:31:49,865 --> 00:31:51,025
What?

270
00:32:06,825 --> 00:32:07,825
Piang.

271
00:32:12,025 --> 00:32:14,345
How did Piang fall down the stairs, Boss?

272
00:32:16,865 --> 00:32:18,625
Piang…

273
00:32:22,025 --> 00:32:24,185
Piang…

274
00:32:27,705 --> 00:32:30,225
She's still heartbroken over you.

275
00:32:30,305 --> 00:32:32,025
She wasn't paying attention.

276
00:32:40,545 --> 00:32:42,745
Why was she moved to
a recovery room already?

277
00:32:42,825 --> 00:32:44,985
Did the ER doctor examine her thoroughly?

278
00:32:46,505 --> 00:32:47,745
Well…

279
00:32:48,545 --> 00:32:49,745
Yes.

280
00:32:50,305 --> 00:32:52,745
But don't worry.

281
00:32:52,825 --> 00:32:55,505
I've taken over Piang's case.

282
00:32:55,585 --> 00:32:57,185
If anything comes up,

283
00:32:57,265 --> 00:32:58,625
I'll take care of her myself.

284
00:32:59,305 --> 00:33:02,345
I see. But aren't you a cardiologist?

285
00:33:05,905 --> 00:33:06,825
I am.

286
00:33:16,345 --> 00:33:18,505
-My head…
-Piang.

287
00:33:18,585 --> 00:33:20,625
My head feels like it's going to explode.

288
00:33:20,705 --> 00:33:21,585
Piang.

289
00:33:21,665 --> 00:33:23,585
Namking, what do we do?

290
00:33:25,065 --> 00:33:26,385
Mud.

291
00:33:27,705 --> 00:33:29,185
Namking.

292
00:33:29,825 --> 00:33:31,225
What's going on?

293
00:33:38,545 --> 00:33:39,905
Who are you?

294
00:33:39,985 --> 00:33:43,585
Who are you?

295
00:34:00,785 --> 00:34:01,745
My head…

296
00:34:05,225 --> 00:34:08,824
Piang suffered a head injury not long ago.

297
00:34:09,505 --> 00:34:11,025
Now that she's hit it again,

298
00:34:11,105 --> 00:34:12,744
even though it wasn't severe,

299
00:34:13,344 --> 00:34:15,625
it can still cause symptoms like this.

300
00:34:16,665 --> 00:34:20,105
Medically, it's called
post-traumatic amnesia,

301
00:34:20,185 --> 00:34:24,225
which is temporary memory loss
after an accident.

302
00:34:25,344 --> 00:34:28,545
The patient remembers almost everything

303
00:34:28,625 --> 00:34:30,545
except certain events

304
00:34:30,625 --> 00:34:34,344
or certain people they've forgotten.

305
00:34:36,304 --> 00:34:37,945
Temporary?

306
00:34:38,025 --> 00:34:40,385
So she'll remember me again?

307
00:34:40,465 --> 00:34:41,744
Mm.

308
00:34:43,105 --> 00:34:44,585
Yes.

309
00:34:44,665 --> 00:34:46,545
But you'll have to be patient.

310
00:34:47,905 --> 00:34:52,065
Though if you want my advice,
don't wait for her.

311
00:34:54,824 --> 00:34:55,945
Why?

312
00:34:56,945 --> 00:34:59,625
The day she confessed to you,

313
00:34:59,705 --> 00:35:01,665
you turned her down.

314
00:35:02,345 --> 00:35:04,585
That means you don't love her.

315
00:35:05,385 --> 00:35:07,305
So why wait?

316
00:35:07,385 --> 00:35:12,625
This is your chance
to let her go for good.

317
00:35:15,905 --> 00:35:18,345
Thanks for the advice.

318
00:35:18,425 --> 00:35:19,825
But I'll wait for her.

319
00:35:20,705 --> 00:35:22,865
And I won't just sit around.

320
00:35:22,945 --> 00:35:27,185
I'll do everything I can
to help Piang remember me again.

321
00:35:31,665 --> 00:35:33,065
I'll get going then.

322
00:35:33,145 --> 00:35:34,385
Okay.

323
00:35:48,145 --> 00:35:50,065
You really don't remember me?

324
00:35:52,745 --> 00:35:54,265
I'm the one you loved,

325
00:35:55,025 --> 00:35:56,905
the one you always chased.

326
00:35:59,985 --> 00:36:01,025
No way.

327
00:36:01,105 --> 00:36:03,985
Piangrawin would never. I just sit here

328
00:36:04,065 --> 00:36:06,025
and people hit on me every day.

329
00:36:07,065 --> 00:36:08,865
I'd never chase anyone.

330
00:36:09,785 --> 00:36:11,305
But I'm telling the truth.

331
00:36:12,665 --> 00:36:15,745
Not long ago, you told me you loved me.

332
00:36:16,625 --> 00:36:18,025
And I…

333
00:36:19,225 --> 00:36:20,225
I…

334
00:36:21,305 --> 00:36:22,345
What?

335
00:36:27,865 --> 00:36:29,385
I love you too.

336
00:36:33,625 --> 00:36:34,865
All this time,

337
00:36:34,945 --> 00:36:36,545
I was in denial.

338
00:36:36,625 --> 00:36:39,025
I never admitted my feelings.

339
00:36:40,225 --> 00:36:42,305
So why now?

340
00:36:42,905 --> 00:36:46,945
Because I already lost you once.

341
00:36:47,025 --> 00:36:48,705
That's when I realized

342
00:36:48,785 --> 00:36:51,905
how painful it is to live without you.

343
00:36:54,345 --> 00:36:56,665
I don't want to lose you again.

344
00:37:01,025 --> 00:37:02,145
Here.

345
00:37:03,225 --> 00:37:04,225
Look.

346
00:37:06,145 --> 00:37:08,505
You wrote this to me.

347
00:37:12,585 --> 00:37:14,225
It's delicious.

348
00:37:14,305 --> 00:37:16,385
But the chef is even sweeter.

349
00:37:17,305 --> 00:37:19,745
I'd love to taste more.

350
00:37:19,825 --> 00:37:22,945
Whenever you're ready, just let me know.

351
00:37:41,105 --> 00:37:42,425
Ew.

352
00:37:42,505 --> 00:37:44,665
That's way too flirty.

353
00:37:47,025 --> 00:37:48,985
By the way, what's your name?

354
00:37:52,065 --> 00:37:52,905
My name is Song.

355
00:37:53,745 --> 00:37:54,945
Song.

356
00:37:56,505 --> 00:37:58,425
I don't think I love you.

357
00:37:59,105 --> 00:38:01,225
I probably just watched too many K-dramas

358
00:38:01,305 --> 00:38:03,025
and wanted to copy them.

359
00:38:10,905 --> 00:38:12,385
Piang.

360
00:38:14,185 --> 00:38:15,745
Ploy, Ple.

361
00:38:15,825 --> 00:38:17,625
-Namprow.
-Hi.

362
00:38:17,705 --> 00:38:19,185
When did you all get here?

363
00:38:19,265 --> 00:38:20,585
I came with Ple.

364
00:38:21,745 --> 00:38:24,465
I brought you some fruit and snacks.

365
00:38:24,545 --> 00:38:26,705
Thank you, Namprow.

366
00:38:27,945 --> 00:38:29,425
Does your head still hurt?

367
00:38:30,105 --> 00:38:33,025
It does, but I'm feeling much better.

368
00:38:33,625 --> 00:38:35,385
You'll be better soon.

369
00:38:35,465 --> 00:38:36,945
Thank you.

370
00:38:37,025 --> 00:38:38,265
Do you need anything else?

371
00:38:51,545 --> 00:38:54,025
You look like a lost puppy, Song.

372
00:38:55,625 --> 00:38:56,585
Ready?

373
00:38:56,665 --> 00:38:59,985
Our mission starts now.

374
00:39:07,105 --> 00:39:08,345
Song.

375
00:39:09,145 --> 00:39:10,985
Why do you look so down?

376
00:39:11,065 --> 00:39:12,945
Don't tell me you've given up.

377
00:39:13,025 --> 00:39:14,425
I haven't.

378
00:39:15,345 --> 00:39:16,985
I'm just thinking.

379
00:39:17,065 --> 00:39:18,985
I don't give up that easily.

380
00:39:23,265 --> 00:39:27,625
Hey, did you and Piang ever
share any special moments?

381
00:39:28,225 --> 00:39:29,265
The good or bad kind?

382
00:39:29,345 --> 00:39:31,825
Good kind, of course.

383
00:39:40,945 --> 00:39:42,265
Yeah.

384
00:39:42,345 --> 00:39:43,305
Why?

385
00:39:43,825 --> 00:39:47,425
I think we should recreate those moments

386
00:39:47,505 --> 00:39:48,825
to trigger her memory.

387
00:39:48,905 --> 00:39:51,065
It might work.

388
00:39:56,745 --> 00:39:58,425
I agree with Namprow.

389
00:40:05,305 --> 00:40:06,545
Um…

390
00:40:06,625 --> 00:40:08,745
But will she go along with it?

391
00:40:09,345 --> 00:40:11,625
We'll just have to lure her in.

392
00:40:12,465 --> 00:40:13,865
Don't worry.

393
00:40:13,945 --> 00:40:15,425
We'll help you.

394
00:40:17,385 --> 00:40:18,305
Fighting!

395
00:40:29,025 --> 00:40:30,345
Piang.

396
00:40:36,625 --> 00:40:40,345
Piang, Ple and I
are going on a trip next week.

397
00:40:40,425 --> 00:40:42,065
We'd love you to come with us.

398
00:40:43,225 --> 00:40:44,345
Would that be okay?

399
00:40:45,025 --> 00:40:45,905
Of course.

400
00:40:45,985 --> 00:40:49,225
Ever since we helped you
at the matcha café,

401
00:40:49,305 --> 00:40:51,985
we haven't had the chance
to travel together.

402
00:40:53,665 --> 00:40:54,745
Please come with us.

403
00:40:58,425 --> 00:40:59,985
By the way,

404
00:41:01,225 --> 00:41:03,345
is Song coming too?

405
00:41:06,305 --> 00:41:07,425
She is.

406
00:41:07,505 --> 00:41:10,265
Song was one of the people
who helped you at the café.

407
00:41:10,345 --> 00:41:14,265
She also created
your café's signature drink.

408
00:41:15,225 --> 00:41:16,225
Really?

409
00:41:18,025 --> 00:41:19,265
I don't remember that.

410
00:41:25,265 --> 00:41:26,705
<i>Hang in there, Song.</i>

411
00:41:29,025 --> 00:41:30,065
Mm.

412
00:42:08,505 --> 00:42:10,065
We're all staying in the same room?

413
00:42:11,665 --> 00:42:12,985
That's right.

414
00:42:13,065 --> 00:42:15,225
Why waste money on separate rooms?

415
00:42:15,745 --> 00:42:18,665
Where are Ploy and Ple staying?

416
00:42:19,265 --> 00:42:21,345
They can't make it after all.

417
00:42:21,425 --> 00:42:24,625
They just texted that something came up.

418
00:42:25,385 --> 00:42:27,025
You must be tired from the trip.

419
00:42:27,105 --> 00:42:29,225
Why don't you soak in the tub first?

420
00:42:29,305 --> 00:42:30,545
I'll bathe you.

421
00:42:33,345 --> 00:42:34,745
No, thanks.

422
00:42:34,825 --> 00:42:36,825
I'm an adult. I can do it myself.

423
00:43:11,505 --> 00:43:13,265
What are you doing?

424
00:43:13,945 --> 00:43:16,105
We've been here together before,

425
00:43:16,185 --> 00:43:18,625
and we slept like this.

426
00:43:19,505 --> 00:43:22,145
Can you stay still for a while?

427
00:44:35,665 --> 00:44:37,225
Keep your hands like this.

428
00:44:38,145 --> 00:44:39,785
Don't move them down.

429
00:44:41,945 --> 00:44:43,025
Otherwise, I'll stop.

430
00:44:45,385 --> 00:44:46,905
And…

431
00:44:48,905 --> 00:44:50,145
you have to endure it

432
00:44:52,105 --> 00:44:54,065
until I'm satisfied.

433
00:45:23,105 --> 00:45:24,385
Get out.

434
00:45:25,705 --> 00:45:28,145
Who do you think you are,
ordering me around?

435
00:45:30,625 --> 00:45:33,745
Don't get the wrong idea.
Just because I share a room with you,

436
00:45:33,825 --> 00:45:35,185
doesn't mean you get to do this.

437
00:45:36,025 --> 00:45:37,745
Listen carefully.

438
00:45:37,825 --> 00:45:39,825
I'm not that easy.

439
00:45:42,065 --> 00:45:43,025
Piang.

440
00:45:45,425 --> 00:45:46,545
Piang.

441
00:45:47,425 --> 00:45:49,025
I'm sorry.

442
00:45:49,105 --> 00:45:51,705
I never thought you were easy.

443
00:45:51,785 --> 00:45:53,785
Everything I did

444
00:45:53,865 --> 00:45:55,905
was only because I wanted you
to remember me.

445
00:45:58,225 --> 00:46:00,025
Please stop trying.

446
00:46:00,105 --> 00:46:02,545
Can't you see?
I'm only missing memories of you.

447
00:46:02,625 --> 00:46:06,225
Maybe it's because the time
we spent together

448
00:46:07,385 --> 00:46:10,345
was the worst time of my life.

449
00:46:11,385 --> 00:46:13,105
I admit it.

450
00:46:13,185 --> 00:46:15,545
I treated you terribly back then.

451
00:46:16,865 --> 00:46:17,865
But…

452
00:46:17,945 --> 00:46:20,345
I really don't want you to forget me.

453
00:46:23,985 --> 00:46:26,185
I want you to remember me.

454
00:46:26,265 --> 00:46:27,945
So you'll know

455
00:46:28,025 --> 00:46:30,625
I'm not the same Song anymore.

456
00:46:31,225 --> 00:46:32,905
The one who was stubborn

457
00:46:33,505 --> 00:46:36,265
and kept running from her own heart.

458
00:46:36,905 --> 00:46:39,225
I'm a new Song now.

459
00:46:40,105 --> 00:46:42,425
Someone who's ready to make you happy

460
00:46:43,505 --> 00:46:45,545
and ready to love you

461
00:46:45,625 --> 00:46:47,465
with no conditions.

462
00:46:49,305 --> 00:46:51,145
Do you really love me?

463
00:46:53,225 --> 00:46:54,345
I do.

464
00:47:04,505 --> 00:47:06,425
Then say it five more times.

465
00:47:07,905 --> 00:47:09,945
I love you.

466
00:47:10,025 --> 00:47:11,505
I love you.

467
00:47:11,585 --> 00:47:13,345
I love you.

468
00:47:13,425 --> 00:47:14,625
I…

469
00:47:18,265 --> 00:47:19,145
Wait.

470
00:47:19,785 --> 00:47:20,785
You…

471
00:47:25,185 --> 00:47:26,745
Ding-dong!

472
00:47:26,825 --> 00:47:28,865
You got played.

473
00:47:29,705 --> 00:47:31,105
What do you mean?

474
00:47:31,985 --> 00:47:34,105
I never had amnesia.

475
00:47:35,265 --> 00:47:38,425
I staged everything to get back at you.

476
00:47:40,105 --> 00:47:42,025
Because if I hadn't,

477
00:47:42,105 --> 00:47:45,185
I would've never heard you say,

478
00:47:45,985 --> 00:47:48,105
"I love you."

479
00:47:48,705 --> 00:47:49,745
What about the others?

480
00:47:51,225 --> 00:47:52,865
They were in on it too.

481
00:47:55,505 --> 00:47:56,985
Wait.

482
00:47:59,225 --> 00:48:02,585
You can't get mad and run away again.

483
00:48:02,665 --> 00:48:05,545
We've been chasing each other long enough.

484
00:48:06,185 --> 00:48:08,025
If you leave again,

485
00:48:08,745 --> 00:48:11,065
there won't be another chance.

486
00:48:13,505 --> 00:48:14,945
I'm not running away.

487
00:48:15,825 --> 00:48:17,345
I'm just thinking

488
00:48:19,945 --> 00:48:22,625
about how to punish you.

489
00:48:31,465 --> 00:48:33,225
What's taking you so long?

490
00:49:25,585 --> 00:49:28,145
MISSION ACCOMPLISHED

491
00:49:28,225 --> 00:49:30,345
<i>Mission accomplished.</i>

492
00:49:33,065 --> 00:49:35,985
<i>The two of us helped Song and Piang</i>

493
00:49:36,065 --> 00:49:37,705
find their way to each other.

494
00:49:37,785 --> 00:49:40,225
So why, when it's our turn,

495
00:49:41,465 --> 00:49:42,945
are you letting go?

496
00:49:43,025 --> 00:49:44,945
Let's fight for us together.

497
00:50:09,185 --> 00:50:11,465
<i>The pain you're going through now…</i>

498
00:50:11,985 --> 00:50:14,105
You've already survived it once.

499
00:50:14,185 --> 00:50:15,985
<i>Don't let it hurt you again.</i>

500
00:50:45,705 --> 00:50:47,225
Ple, are you trying to kill me?

501
00:50:54,905 --> 00:50:57,625
You little brat!
Are you trying to kill me?

502
00:51:09,025 --> 00:51:12,105
Ple, is something wrong?

503
00:51:16,065 --> 00:51:17,425
About my father…

504
00:51:17,505 --> 00:51:19,225
I've made up my mind.

505
00:51:20,585 --> 00:51:22,145
I'm going to report him.

506
00:51:25,225 --> 00:51:26,625
That's the right thing to do.

507
00:51:28,505 --> 00:51:30,225
As for us…

508
00:51:32,305 --> 00:51:35,025
I've… made up my mind too.

509
00:51:38,865 --> 00:51:40,945
Everything you said was true.

510
00:51:41,025 --> 00:51:42,545
The two of us

511
00:51:42,625 --> 00:51:44,825
kept helping other people fall in love.

512
00:51:44,905 --> 00:51:46,425
But when it came to us…

513
00:51:48,785 --> 00:51:49,785
No.

514
00:51:50,505 --> 00:51:51,985
It was me.

515
00:51:52,065 --> 00:51:54,345
I chose to let go of your hand.

516
00:51:55,185 --> 00:51:56,505
Seriously?

517
00:51:58,185 --> 00:51:59,745
When you weren't by my side,

518
00:52:00,665 --> 00:52:02,385
I felt so lonely.

519
00:52:05,905 --> 00:52:07,505
I kept telling myself,

520
00:52:07,585 --> 00:52:09,865
"It'll be better tomorrow."

521
00:52:09,945 --> 00:52:12,225
But when we met again,

522
00:52:13,905 --> 00:52:16,025
my feelings became even clearer.

523
00:52:21,105 --> 00:52:23,265
I realized how much I need you.

524
00:52:23,785 --> 00:52:25,185
Really, Ple?

525
00:52:25,905 --> 00:52:27,945
You didn't seem to care about me.

526
00:52:28,025 --> 00:52:29,905
Ever since I called you,

527
00:52:29,985 --> 00:52:32,225
even when we met at the hospital,

528
00:52:32,905 --> 00:52:34,265
you ignored me.

529
00:52:34,345 --> 00:52:35,705
Yeah, I was putting on an act.

530
00:52:35,785 --> 00:52:37,905
I'm terrible at being honest.
You know that.

531
00:52:45,305 --> 00:52:46,465
Ploy.

532
00:52:49,505 --> 00:52:51,545
Will you come back to me?

533
00:52:54,785 --> 00:52:57,225
By the way, how many drinks have you had?

534
00:52:57,945 --> 00:52:58,945
Why?

535
00:52:59,025 --> 00:53:00,265
I just want to make sure

536
00:53:00,345 --> 00:53:02,465
you're not too drunk
to know what you're saying.

537
00:53:03,025 --> 00:53:04,305
Ploy.

538
00:53:05,025 --> 00:53:07,025
Come back to me.

539
00:53:07,105 --> 00:53:08,345
How could I not?

540
00:53:08,425 --> 00:53:09,985
I've been waiting for this.

541
00:53:41,225 --> 00:53:42,865
The view is beautiful.

542
00:53:48,665 --> 00:53:50,145
Not as beautiful as you.

543
00:54:14,065 --> 00:54:16,385
Once we're married,

544
00:54:16,465 --> 00:54:18,625
we can come here more often.

545
00:54:21,425 --> 00:54:22,465
What?

546
00:54:23,065 --> 00:54:25,305
Are you proposing to me?

547
00:54:27,905 --> 00:54:30,225
Then… where's the ring?

548
00:54:32,265 --> 00:54:33,105
I don't have it.

549
00:54:34,505 --> 00:54:36,905
Then why are you getting my hopes up?

550
00:54:38,625 --> 00:54:40,265
Actually, I already have a ring.

551
00:54:40,865 --> 00:54:42,785
I just didn't bring it with me.

552
00:54:43,665 --> 00:54:47,065
I think
before I put the ring on your finger,

553
00:54:47,145 --> 00:54:48,985
I should ask your grandmother first.

554
00:54:52,145 --> 00:54:53,265
Okay.

555
00:54:56,025 --> 00:54:57,745
I love you.

556
00:55:02,745 --> 00:55:04,425
I love you too.

557
00:55:57,625 --> 00:55:58,465
Oh.

558
00:55:58,545 --> 00:55:59,585
Hey, Piang.

559
00:56:00,585 --> 00:56:01,985
Come dance with me.

560
00:56:02,065 --> 00:56:04,065
You haven't danced with me in ages.

561
00:56:04,145 --> 00:56:05,545
Let me have this dance with her.

562
00:56:07,465 --> 00:56:09,385
If you don't mind,

563
00:56:09,465 --> 00:56:11,145
may I have this dance, Madam?

564
00:56:13,305 --> 00:56:14,265
You can dance?

565
00:56:16,065 --> 00:56:17,065
Yes.

566
00:56:23,665 --> 00:56:24,945
Song.

567
00:56:28,425 --> 00:56:29,625
Oh…

568
00:56:30,825 --> 00:56:33,105
It doesn't look like she can dance.

569
00:56:43,425 --> 00:56:46,185
Song, that's not
how you dance with an elder.

570
00:56:55,505 --> 00:56:57,065
Madam,

571
00:56:58,025 --> 00:57:00,945
I'm sorry for breaking my promise to you.

572
00:57:02,545 --> 00:57:04,585
I really tried,

573
00:57:05,905 --> 00:57:07,785
but I couldn't do it.

574
00:57:09,385 --> 00:57:10,985
I'm in love with Piang.

575
00:57:12,265 --> 00:57:13,425
Very much.

576
00:57:14,625 --> 00:57:17,225
And I'm going to ask her to marry me.

577
00:57:29,705 --> 00:57:32,385
This time, I won't make you any promises.

578
00:57:33,065 --> 00:57:35,065
I'll prove to you

579
00:57:35,625 --> 00:57:37,905
that I truly love your granddaughter.

580
00:57:50,825 --> 00:57:52,625
I won't ask anything of you.

581
00:57:53,865 --> 00:57:57,145
Just don't make her cry again.

582
00:58:00,305 --> 00:58:01,425
Are you finished?

583
00:58:01,505 --> 00:58:02,465
Yes, I am.

584
00:58:02,545 --> 00:58:04,465
So I can get back to
dancing with my teacher.

585
00:58:05,145 --> 00:58:06,425
Otherwise,

586
00:58:07,185 --> 00:58:09,865
people might think

587
00:58:09,945 --> 00:58:13,785
you came to flirt with me,
not my granddaughter.

588
00:58:15,265 --> 00:58:16,545
What?

589
00:58:16,625 --> 00:58:20,345
That's a dance move for couples.

590
00:58:25,825 --> 00:58:28,025
Next time,
if you can't dance, just tell me.

591
00:58:28,705 --> 00:58:30,585
I'll teach you

592
00:58:31,185 --> 00:58:34,025
so you won't embarrass yourself again.

593
00:58:38,105 --> 00:58:39,305
Well…

594
00:58:39,385 --> 00:58:41,145
I'm sorry.

595
00:58:41,225 --> 00:58:43,825
I won't do it again.

596
00:58:43,905 --> 00:58:45,465
Sorry…

597
00:59:08,145 --> 00:59:10,385
There she is.

598
00:59:11,305 --> 00:59:12,305
Grandma.

599
00:59:15,945 --> 00:59:17,225
Your Ladyship.

600
00:59:17,945 --> 00:59:19,425
Piang.

601
00:59:19,985 --> 00:59:21,065
Oh.

602
00:59:21,145 --> 00:59:25,545
So you're
the woman who stole Song's heart.

603
00:59:25,625 --> 00:59:28,185
Oh, my.

604
00:59:28,265 --> 00:59:30,865
What a twist of fate.

605
00:59:30,945 --> 00:59:32,825
Song, remember when

606
00:59:32,905 --> 00:59:34,505
I told you

607
00:59:34,585 --> 00:59:37,025
I once saved a young woman?

608
00:59:37,745 --> 00:59:41,185
That young woman was Piang.

609
00:59:41,265 --> 00:59:42,585
Wait, wait.

610
00:59:43,145 --> 00:59:44,585
What's going on?

611
00:59:44,665 --> 00:59:47,225
And why are you at my house,
Your Ladyship?

612
00:59:47,305 --> 00:59:51,625
Well, I'm here to ask for
your granddaughter's hand

613
00:59:51,705 --> 00:59:54,905
for my granddaughter.

614
00:59:55,585 --> 00:59:57,385
Who's your granddaughter?

615
00:59:57,465 --> 00:59:59,225
-Right here.
-Huh?

616
00:59:59,305 --> 01:00:02,625
Song Sadanun Warakij.

617
01:00:02,705 --> 01:00:08,545
The heir
to the Warakijaruwongs royal family.

618
01:00:11,665 --> 01:00:14,425
-I'm going to faint.
-Grandma!

619
01:00:14,505 --> 01:00:17,065
Why didn't you tell me
who your family was?

620
01:00:17,145 --> 01:00:19,345
Because I didn't want to win you over

621
01:00:19,425 --> 01:00:21,065
with my status or family name.

622
01:00:21,145 --> 01:00:23,825
I wanted you to accept me

623
01:00:23,905 --> 01:00:27,145
for how sincerely I love Piang.

624
01:00:27,225 --> 01:00:29,945
That's my wonderful granddaughter.

625
01:00:30,025 --> 01:00:31,785
That's exactly how it's done.

626
01:00:31,865 --> 01:00:33,825
So, what do you say?

627
01:00:33,905 --> 01:00:36,585
Will you let your granddaughter

628
01:00:36,665 --> 01:00:40,305
marry my granddaughter?

629
01:00:40,385 --> 01:00:41,625
Sure…

630
01:00:41,705 --> 01:00:43,825
Take her already.

631
01:00:47,105 --> 01:00:48,345
What?

632
01:00:48,425 --> 01:00:50,945
Careful, Grandma. Easy.

633
01:01:18,465 --> 01:01:19,585
<i>Isn't it amazing?</i>

634
01:01:19,665 --> 01:01:21,065
It's so good.

635
01:01:27,185 --> 01:01:29,305
<i>I've never had a girlfriend before.</i>

636
01:01:29,945 --> 01:01:31,665
So, will you be my girlfriend?

637
01:02:02,865 --> 01:02:04,385
Hello, Mudmee.

638
01:02:05,465 --> 01:02:08,785
I'm Kwanrin from 124 KT Design.

639
01:02:09,465 --> 01:02:11,865
I'd like to help plan
your sister's wedding.

640
01:02:13,745 --> 01:02:15,745
Is that really why you're here?

641
01:02:22,265 --> 01:02:23,945
Your name is Kwanrin, right?

642
01:02:24,785 --> 01:02:25,985
Yes.

643
01:02:26,065 --> 01:02:28,385
You remember me?

644
01:02:28,465 --> 01:02:29,665
Of course.

645
01:02:30,745 --> 01:02:32,705
I'm the one who broke you two up.

646
01:02:42,625 --> 01:02:44,185
Would it be alright

647
01:02:44,905 --> 01:02:46,425
if I asked you

648
01:02:46,505 --> 01:02:48,745
to get back together
with my granddaughter?

649
01:02:51,065 --> 01:02:52,105
Grandma.

650
01:02:59,265 --> 01:03:03,745
I want to see both of
my granddaughters happy.

651
01:03:07,185 --> 01:03:09,025
Thank you so much, Grandma.

652
01:03:11,585 --> 01:03:12,505
Mudmee.

653
01:03:13,105 --> 01:03:14,745
I'm sorry

654
01:03:14,825 --> 01:03:16,305
for letting go of you

655
01:03:16,385 --> 01:03:18,745
the way I did that day.

656
01:03:20,065 --> 01:03:23,185
Everything happened so suddenly

657
01:03:24,025 --> 01:03:26,105
that I didn't know what to do.

658
01:03:26,185 --> 01:03:28,305
But today,

659
01:03:28,945 --> 01:03:31,065
I'm here to ask for another chance.

660
01:03:32,505 --> 01:03:34,305
I promise

661
01:03:35,185 --> 01:03:37,425
that no matter what we face,

662
01:03:38,145 --> 01:03:39,545
or what obstacles come,

663
01:03:40,345 --> 01:03:42,225
I won't leave you again.

664
01:03:43,185 --> 01:03:44,385
I promise.

665
01:03:49,425 --> 01:03:50,385
I accept.

666
01:03:53,145 --> 01:03:54,505
Then keep your promise.

667
01:03:55,665 --> 01:03:59,465
Look, I've got a witness right here.

668
01:04:00,945 --> 01:04:02,185
You're the witness,

669
01:04:02,265 --> 01:04:04,345
but you're also the biggest obstacle.

670
01:04:04,425 --> 01:04:05,585
You little…

671
01:04:13,585 --> 01:04:15,705
Let's start over.

672
01:04:21,105 --> 01:04:22,505
Okay.

673
01:05:06,545 --> 01:05:08,505
I look beautiful, don't I?

674
01:05:15,905 --> 01:05:17,505
You look beautiful.

675
01:05:21,225 --> 01:05:23,425
You look beautiful too.

676
01:05:35,905 --> 01:05:37,825
Is this Neung?

677
01:05:37,905 --> 01:05:40,265
You two look exactly alike.

678
01:05:43,345 --> 01:05:44,585
Yes.

679
01:05:44,665 --> 01:05:47,145
We look the same

680
01:05:48,185 --> 01:05:49,825
but our personalities are nothing alike.

681
01:06:05,545 --> 01:06:07,305
Song,

682
01:06:07,385 --> 01:06:09,385
can I ask you something?

683
01:06:09,465 --> 01:06:11,265
What happened to Neung?

684
01:06:11,865 --> 01:06:15,105
And… what does it have to do with you?

685
01:06:19,865 --> 01:06:22,785
But if you're not ready to talk about it…

686
01:06:25,585 --> 01:06:27,025
I am.

687
01:06:27,105 --> 01:06:29,265
We're getting married.

688
01:06:29,345 --> 01:06:31,505
I have nothing left to hide from you.

689
01:06:38,065 --> 01:06:39,825
The two of us…

690
01:06:42,225 --> 01:06:44,145
dated the same woman.

691
01:06:44,985 --> 01:06:46,185
What?

692
01:06:47,265 --> 01:06:50,425
-"The same woman?"
-Yes.

693
01:06:51,265 --> 01:06:52,865
But she was a con artist.

694
01:06:53,865 --> 01:06:56,145
She conned us both out of our money.

695
01:06:56,865 --> 01:06:59,545
She used her charm

696
01:06:59,625 --> 01:07:01,625
to make both Neung and me

697
01:07:02,265 --> 01:07:03,905
trust her completely.

698
01:07:05,185 --> 01:07:06,785
Neither of us

699
01:07:06,865 --> 01:07:08,865
ever suspected her.

700
01:07:09,825 --> 01:07:11,145
<i>I missed you so much.</i>

701
01:07:11,225 --> 01:07:12,425
Have you been waiting long?

702
01:07:12,505 --> 01:07:14,225
<i>We loved her so deeply</i>

703
01:07:15,505 --> 01:07:17,665
<i>and gave her everything.</i>

704
01:07:18,185 --> 01:07:19,545
<i>Then one day,</i>

705
01:07:19,625 --> 01:07:22,665
<i>Neung realized something wasn't right.</i>

706
01:07:23,545 --> 01:07:27,105
<i>Eventually, she learned the whole truth.</i>

707
01:07:36,305 --> 01:07:37,785
I was devastated.

708
01:07:46,225 --> 01:07:48,265
But Neung was hurting even more.

709
01:07:52,585 --> 01:07:56,065
She couldn't move past the pain.

710
01:08:06,705 --> 01:08:07,985
In the end,

711
01:08:09,745 --> 01:08:11,865
she made that choice.

712
01:08:16,265 --> 01:08:17,584
After that,

713
01:08:18,544 --> 01:08:20,464
I kept thinking…

714
01:08:20,544 --> 01:08:22,945
If Neung died in misery,

715
01:08:24,345 --> 01:08:27,424
then you didn't deserve
to be happy, right?

716
01:08:28,265 --> 01:08:29,265
That's right.

717
01:08:31,745 --> 01:08:33,584
Especially when it came to love.

718
01:08:33,665 --> 01:08:37,065
That's one reason
I never wanted to love anyone.

719
01:08:37,145 --> 01:08:39,705
Until I met you

720
01:08:39,785 --> 01:08:42,265
and truly fell in love with you.

721
01:08:43,745 --> 01:08:46,065
That's why I ran from my own heart.

722
01:08:47,825 --> 01:08:49,665
I understand.

723
01:08:51,225 --> 01:08:55,185
If I'd known what you'd been through,

724
01:08:56,345 --> 01:08:58,745
I would've never let you go.

725
01:08:58,825 --> 01:09:03,265
No matter how many times you ran from me,

726
01:09:03,345 --> 01:09:05,625
I'd still stay by your side.

727
01:09:12,705 --> 01:09:13,705
Thank you.

728
01:09:14,985 --> 01:09:16,865
For being here.

729
01:09:18,785 --> 01:09:19,985
Yes.

730
01:09:20,945 --> 01:09:25,185
And I'll stay by your side
for the rest of my life.

731
01:10:10,825 --> 01:10:12,265
Thank you.

732
01:10:15,265 --> 01:10:16,625
Marry me.

733
01:10:18,185 --> 01:10:19,185
Yes.

734
01:10:39,865 --> 01:10:41,865
Thank you.

735
01:10:58,865 --> 01:11:02,665
Isn't this the perfect moment for a kiss?

736
01:11:02,745 --> 01:11:06,185
-Kiss!
-Kiss!

737
01:11:06,265 --> 01:11:08,945
-Kiss!
-Kiss!

738
01:11:09,025 --> 01:11:12,105
-Kiss!
-Kiss!

739
01:11:28,345 --> 01:11:30,025
Are you ready?

740
01:11:30,705 --> 01:11:33,345
-Mud's over here!
-Piang, throw it this way!

741
01:11:33,425 --> 01:11:35,145
-Mud is over here!
-Three, two…

742
01:11:41,265 --> 01:11:43,985
-That's it!
-Get married next!

743
01:11:49,185 --> 01:11:50,665
Come on, that's it!

744
01:11:57,745 --> 01:11:59,785
-Grandma!
-Grandma!

745
01:11:59,865 --> 01:12:02,785
-Everyone, get in the frame!
-Come on, my dear.

746
01:12:11,065 --> 01:12:13,065
-Don't block the camera.
-Okay.

747
01:12:13,145 --> 01:12:15,385
Five, four, three… Okay!

748
01:12:33,225 --> 01:12:35,025
Isn't it winter?

749
01:12:35,665 --> 01:12:36,825
Where's the fog?

750
01:12:37,425 --> 01:12:39,185
It's nighttime.

751
01:12:39,265 --> 01:12:40,865
There won't be any fog now.

752
01:12:41,985 --> 01:12:43,385
I was kidding.

753
01:12:45,705 --> 01:12:47,745
So what star are you waiting to see?

754
01:12:47,825 --> 01:12:49,865
The lovers' star.

755
01:12:53,425 --> 01:12:55,665
You've been watching another series,
haven't you?

756
01:12:57,465 --> 01:12:58,665
Well…

757
01:12:58,745 --> 01:13:01,385
The same one with the wine scene.

758
01:13:03,945 --> 01:13:05,945
So you know it doesn't work now?

759
01:13:06,025 --> 01:13:07,585
True.

760
01:13:07,665 --> 01:13:10,305
I can't see that star.
Where's the lovers' star?

761
01:13:15,225 --> 01:13:16,585
It's right here.

762
01:13:19,145 --> 01:13:21,265
Forget that silly star.

763
01:13:21,345 --> 01:13:23,305
Let's go back to our room.

764
01:13:23,825 --> 01:13:26,625
My hand's fully healed now.

765
01:13:34,985 --> 01:13:35,825
Wait.

766
01:13:38,545 --> 01:13:40,425
Will you dance with me first?

767
01:13:40,505 --> 01:13:42,865
This time, I'll lead.

768
01:13:44,345 --> 01:13:45,585
Of course.

769
01:13:45,665 --> 01:13:49,145
I'd like to see how well
Grandma trained you.

770
01:14:21,185 --> 01:14:25,465
Piang, thank you for loving me.

771
01:14:26,905 --> 01:14:30,025
And for giving me the courage
to be happy again.

772
01:14:32,305 --> 01:14:35,385
I'm so lucky to have met you, Piang.

773
01:14:35,945 --> 01:14:38,625
I'm lucky too

774
01:14:38,705 --> 01:14:40,225
to have met you, Song.

775
01:14:41,585 --> 01:14:42,505
Really?

776
01:14:43,185 --> 01:14:44,505
How so?

777
01:14:48,585 --> 01:14:49,745
I don't know.

778
01:14:50,585 --> 01:14:52,625
Isn't that what I'm supposed to say?

779
01:14:53,785 --> 01:14:56,265
You're so adorable, you little goof.

